build infrastructure,<br />not in fs/Makefile.<br /><br />That said, we *probably* should also look at making anything that the<br />kernel build uses replace something like<br /><br />  #ifdef linux  (or __linux__)<br /><br />with<br /><br />  #if defined(linux) || defined(__KERNEL__)<br /><br />so that we can always rely on just the normal __KERNEL__ define rather<br />than depending on the compiler being properly set up for<br />cross-compiling for Linux.<br /><br />But your patch is definitely wrong.<br /><br />                      Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
